techmeme.title: At a three-day Intel event in Arizona, executives repeatedly asserted that 18A is the most advanced chip production tech developed and deployed in the US (Ian King/Bloomberg)

Intel says 18A-based Panther Lake chips can deliver 50% more performance at similar power to Lunar Lake chips, details RibbonFET efficiency gains, and more (Jeffrey Kampman/Tom's Hardware)
Inside Intel's new 700-acre factories in the Arizona desert, which cost $32B and are starting large-scale 18A chip production, as it seeks to impress customers (Michael Acton/Financial Times)
Intel unveils Panther Lake, or Intel Core Ultra Series 3, the first chip built on its 18A process, coming to laptops and handhelds in late 2025 and early 2026 (Sean Hollister/The Verge)
